DATA2410 Reliable Transport Protocol (DRTP)

To run the application:

1. Run the simple-topo.py with the command python3 simple-topo.py. This runs the mininet. But, you must be logged in as a root to run it.
2. Then, open the h1 and h2 terminal with the help of xterm h1 h2.
3. See the ip address of the h2 with the help of ifconfig. Then, invoke the server in the h2 terminal by using 
python3 application.py -s -i 10.0.1.2 -p 12345 (-d 3)
-s invokes the server, -i is the ip address of the h2 node and -p is the port number where the application is running. -d flag is the optional argument to discard the packet with the respective packet number. In, this case packet number 3.
4. Invoke the client in the h1 terminal with the help of
python3 application.py -c -f filename -i 10.0.1.2 -p 12345 (-w 5)
-c invokes the client, -f takes the filename which is getting transmitted, -i is the ip address of the h2 node and -p is the port number where the application is running. -w is the optional flag that changes the sliding window size, by default its value is given 3 in the application.
